            "body": "Ah no, it's just you can't do that after the login event , that's too soon, the entities are not loaded. Try with the spawn event, use a setTimeout or do that action on a command like in mineflayer examples ;)\r\nThat function is completely independent of rbot.\r\n\r\nSomething like that should work:\r\n```js\r\nbot.on('spawn', function() {\r\n   setTimeout(function(){\r\n    var entity=nearestEntity(bot.entities)\r\n    bot.attack(entity);\r\n  },3000);\r\n});\r\n\r\nfunction nearestEntity(entities)\r\n{\r\n    var r=entities.reduce(function(acc,entity)\r\n    {\r\n        var d=entity.position.distanceTo(bot.entity.position);\r\n        if(d<acc[1])\r\n        {\r\n            acc[0]=entity;\r\n            acc[1]=d;\r\n        }\r\n        return acc;\r\n    },[null,1000000]);\r\n    return r[0];\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n(see https://github.com/andrewrk/mineflayer/issues/328 about the need to use a timeout after spawn event)",
