        {
            "body": "Ah, that was pretty close but not quite correct. In jumper.js there is a correct example of that. You can try it (just say attack and it will attack the closest entity)\r\nIf you want the bot to attack at spawn, just do:\r\n```js\r\nbot.on('spawn', function() {\r\n  setTimeout(function(){\r\n    var entity = nearestEntity();\r\n    if(entity) {\r\n      bot.attack(entity, true);\r\n    } else {\r\n      bot.chat('no nearby entities');\r\n    }\r\n  },3000);\r\n});\r\n\r\nfunction nearestEntity(type) {\r\n  var id, entity, dist;\r\n  var best = null;\r\n  var bestDistance = null;\r\n  for(id in bot.entities) {\r\n    entity = bot.entities[id];\r\n    if(type && entity.type !== type) continue;\r\n    if(entity === bot.entity) continue;\r\n    dist = bot.entity.position.distanceTo(entity.position);\r\n    if(!best || dist < bestDistance) {\r\n      best = entity;\r\n      bestDistance = dist;\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n  return best;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n(I tested this one, it works)",
